Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of estimating the lengths of memory words in a stochastic process based on observations of a single sample. This involves information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques for estimating the length of the longest minimal memory word. The problem also involves the study of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.CC) for identifying memory words. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the field of signal processing (cs.SI) for analyzing and processing stochastic signals.
